1
00:01:51,470 --> 00:01:53,590
I'm starving...

2
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:56,220
When the hell are
we gonna reach land?

3
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:57,100
Who knows?

4
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:00,730
We're just letting the wind
and waves carry us, after all...

5
00:02:01,770 --> 00:02:06,980
Isn't it a little weird that the future
King of the Pirates can't even navigate?!

6
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:09,980
It's not weird. I've just
been drifting around.

7
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:14,110
What about you? Don't bounty
hunters travel the seas?

8
00:02:14,110 --> 00:02:17,990
I don't remember ever calling
myself a bounty hunter.

9
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:22,330
I set out to sea in search
of a certain man

10
00:02:22,330 --> 00:02:24,540
but couldn't find my village again.

11
00:02:25,170 --> 00:02:28,800
Eventually, I just went after
pirate ships to earn a living.

12
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,460
Oh. So you got lost.

13
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:32,840
You don't have to put it like that!

14
00:02:40,350 --> 00:02:42,020
We scored big again!

15
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:44,940
Captain Buggy won't be mad
once he sees all this!

16
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:46,270
Huh?

17
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:47,810
Hey, check it out...

18
00:02:47,810 --> 00:02:49,020
– Hm?
– Huh?

19
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,820
What's with that boat?

20
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,670
I-It's a girl!

21
00:03:09,670 --> 00:03:11,500
Hey! What's wrong with you?

22
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:17,140
Oh! Am I dreaming?

23
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:20,220
Running into someone
on this wide, open sea...

24
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:23,100
I-I don't know who
you are, but... water...

25
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:25,440
Might I ask for a cup of water?

26
00:03:25,690 --> 00:03:27,900
I can pay you however
much you want.

27
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:30,020
Please, help me!

28
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:32,860
No problem! We'll help you out!

29
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:36,280
But not until we see
that treasure of yours!

30
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,740
Don't mind us!

31
00:03:41,830 --> 00:03:44,700
I can't get it open...
Oh, like this?

32
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:53,630
Hell, keep the whole boat if you'd like!

33
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,010
Our boat!

34
00:03:56,010 --> 00:03:58,180
You tricked us!

35
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:02,970
There's a cold front with
low clouds to the south!

36
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:06,230
We can expect some intense
wind and squalls very soon!

37
00:04:06,230 --> 00:04:08,940
Small boats should be careful not to capsize.

38
00:04:20,990 --> 00:04:22,280
Bingo!

39
00:04:23,410 --> 00:04:24,240
See ya!

40
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,700
I'll just help myself to your treasure!

41
00:04:27,290 --> 00:04:29,210
Wait! You bitch!

42
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:31,630
We'll get you for this...

43
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,880
Man, I'm hungry.

44
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,090
A bird...?

45
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,390
Let's eat it!

46
00:04:41,390 --> 00:04:43,300
Huh? How?

47
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:45,140
Leave it to me!

48
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:47,600
Gum-Gum...

49
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,060
Rocket!

50
00:04:50,270 --> 00:04:51,730
So that's how.

51
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:01,360
Help!

52
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,950
Moron! What the hell are you doing?!

53
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,580
Hey! Stop!

54
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:13,460
You on the ship! Stop!

55
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:15,920
Castaways, at a time like this?!

56
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:18,260
I can't stop! Just jump in!

57
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:20,680
– What?!
– What?!

58
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,390
Good job, you made it!

59
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,760
– Were you trying to hit us?!
– Were you trying to hit us?!

60
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:29,270
Hey! Stop the boat!

61
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:33,020
We're members of the great
Buggy the Clown's crew!

62
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:34,610
This boat is ours now!

63
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:36,150
Huh?!

64
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:43,030
We had no idea you were
the famous Pirate Hunter Zoro!

65
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:45,320
– Forgive our rudeness!
– Forgive our rudeness!

66
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:48,450
Thanks to you clowns,
I lost sight of my friend.

67
00:05:48,450 --> 00:05:50,160
Just keep rowing!

68
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,210
– Yessir!
– Yessir!

69
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:55,590
Knowing Luffy, he'll manage
something once he spots land.

70
00:05:56,670 --> 00:05:58,750
But still...

71
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,460
What do we do now, Bro?

72
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:01,720
Good question...

73
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:06,890
If Captain Buggy finds out some girl
stole our boat and treasure...

74
00:06:06,890 --> 00:06:07,720
Y-Yeah...

75
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,930
Hm? Who's this Buggy guy?

76
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:12,980
Huh?! You've never heard
of Buggy the Clown?!

77
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:14,600
Nope.

78
00:06:14,850 --> 00:06:17,610
He's the captain of our crew!

79
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:24,360
As if he wasn't already terrifying,
he also ate a devil fruit!

80
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,380
Yes! I finally got it!

81
00:06:45,890 --> 00:06:47,220
Get back here, you wench!

82
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:48,640
Hey, girl! That's our map!

83
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:53,140
We just stole that map
to the Grand Line!

84
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:56,480
Dammit! If we don't get it back,
we're dead meat!

85
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:59,110
I'd hate to be a target
for the captain's cannonballs!

86
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:05,240
Captain Buggy!

87
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,450
I see something
in the sky above the port!

88
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,620
Shoot it down!

89
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,250
Wh-What the...?

90
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:29,050
Wh-What?!

91
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:30,810
What was that?!

92
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:32,520
Someone fell from the sky!

93
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:36,730
Dammit! Why's someone
shooting cannonballs at me?!

94
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,440
Well, I'm free now!

95
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:46,700
That was a pretty cool ride!

96
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:52,030
Ah... I'm starving...

97
00:07:52,030 --> 00:07:53,290
B-Boss!

98
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:55,040
You came to save me!

99
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:55,620
Huh?

100
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,830
Who are you?

101
00:08:00,210 --> 00:08:03,050
Sorry, but they're all yours now!

102
00:08:05,550 --> 00:08:06,880
Hey! She's getting away!

103
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,550
That's okay! Her boss is right here!

104
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:11,100
Oh, I see!

105
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:13,470
Covering for your lackey, huh?!

106
00:08:13,470 --> 00:08:16,100
Say, is there any place
to eat around here?

107
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,100
Quit screwing around, kid!

108
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:30,030
Hands off my treasure!

109
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:31,780
– You bastard!
– You bastard!

110
00:08:31,780 --> 00:08:33,910
I wonder if they killed that guy...

111
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:37,250
Gum-Gum Pistol!

112
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,710
Wow!

113
00:08:45,710 --> 00:08:47,380
You're pretty tough!

114
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:53,220
They had sabers,
but you knocked them flat!

115
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:56,270
Hey! You're the one who...!
Who are you?

116
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:59,390
I'm a thief who steals from pirates!

117
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,520
The name's Nami!

118
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,440
Hey, wanna team up?!

119
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:05,900
Nope. I don't feel like
teaming up with you.

120
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,610
W-W-Wait!

121
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,360
Wait, I said!

122
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:16,840
They still haven't caught the thief?!

123
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:23,170
Th-They should be pursuing her
as we speak, Captain Buggy! Yes!

124
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:28,960
How'd she steal the map so easily?! Huh?!

125
00:09:30,420 --> 00:09:35,470
Just when we were about to enter
the Grand Line to cause some chaos!

126
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:40,230
A-Actually, someone forgot
to close the shack by mistake.

127
00:09:41,020 --> 00:09:42,020
What did you say?!

128
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:44,650
S-Someone forgot to close
the shack by mistake.

129
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:47,210
Whose nose is tacky 'n fake?!

130
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:51,860
Do you find this nose funny?!

131
00:09:51,860 --> 00:09:53,740
Like a fake nose?!

132
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,830
Th-That's not what I said at all!

133
00:09:55,830 --> 00:09:58,290
It's like a huge red ball?!

134
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,120
H-Help!

135
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:09,630
H-Here it comes...

136
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:11,880
H-His devil fruit power...

137
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:19,810
Who am I?

138
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:23,190
C-Captain Buggy...

139
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,650
What happens to mutineers?

140
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:33,610
A flashy death awaits them...

141
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:35,570
Please forgive me!

142
00:10:35,570 --> 00:10:38,490
I'll never say it again!

143
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:41,080
Please forgive me!

144
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:48,040
I'll overlook your verbal slipup
and forgive you just this once.

145
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,880
Now get that map back!

146
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,340
And if you screw up...!
Well, you know the rest.

147
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:55,680
– Aye, aye, Captain Buggy!
– Aye, aye, Captain Buggy!

148
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,270
Yum!

149
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:04,770
Do you live alone in this house?

150
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:07,860
I'm not actually from this town.

151
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:11,110
Everyone here ran away
because of Buggy.

152
00:11:11,820 --> 00:11:12,740
So you're a thief.

153
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,240
How rude!

154
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:17,320
I'm a thief who only
steals from pirates!

155
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:20,120
Don't compare me to some burglar!

156
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,040
But a thief's a thief.

157
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:29,040
My goal is to earn 100 million berries,
no matter what it takes.

158
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:32,500
What do you need that much for?

159
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,760
That's a secret!

160
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:39,220
But with a map to the Grand Line,
100 million is within reach!

161
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:41,470
A map?

162
00:11:41,470 --> 00:11:42,890
Are you a navigator?!

163
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:46,520
Much more skilled than
your average navigator!

164
00:11:47,350 --> 00:11:49,100
Oh, that's perfect!

165
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:52,440
Do you wanna be our navigator?!

166
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,440
Really?

167
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,900
Yeah! Join our pirate crew!

168
00:11:56,650 --> 00:11:57,400
No!

169
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:01,530
So you're a pirate?

170
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:05,870
Yeah. I swore to the person
who gave me this straw hat

171
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:08,210
that I'd gather a crew
and become a pirate!

172
00:12:09,250 --> 00:12:12,250
There's nothing I hate more
in this world than pirates!

173
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,960
I only like money and tangerines!

174
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:16,260
C'mon. You gotta be our navigator.

175
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,630
No means no.

176
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:19,390
No, huh?

177
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:22,550
Hey, any sign of her?!

178
00:12:22,550 --> 00:12:24,520
I can't find her anywhere!

179
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,770
Where'd that thief girl go?!

180
00:12:26,770 --> 00:12:29,440
We're in big trouble if we don't
get that map back!

181
00:12:30,350 --> 00:12:33,270
I gotta do something about them.

182
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:38,030
Well, I might consider it if you
agree to certain conditions!

183
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:40,530
Hm? Really?! I'll do anything!

184
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:44,450
I want you to come with me
to see a pirate named Buggy.

185
00:12:44,450 --> 00:12:45,200
But...

186
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:50,790
Why am I tied up?

187
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:52,670
It's just rope. Is there a problem?

188
00:12:52,670 --> 00:12:54,550
Hmm... Nah!

189
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:56,760
I was hoping to meet other pirates!

190
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,800
Let's go!

191
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:00,130
Hold on, now!

192
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:02,930
What?!

193
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:04,970
The thief got away?!

194
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,730
– Please forgive us, Captain!
– Please forgive us, Captain!

195
00:13:08,730 --> 00:13:13,110
All three of you are pathetic!
Now die with some flashy flair!

196
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,610
Captain Buggy!

197
00:13:16,610 --> 00:13:17,610
What is it?!

198
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,570
That thief from earlier
came back on her own!

199
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:21,570
What?!

200
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,160
That's them!

201
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,870
She's the one who stole the map!

202
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:36,000
I've captured your thief,
Captain Buggy the Clown!

203
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,340
Here's your map back!

204
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:39,760
I appreciate it.

205
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:42,300
But why the change of heart?

206
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:46,760
My boss and I had a fight.

207
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,810
I'm fed up with him!

208
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:51,140
Please let me join your crew!

209
00:13:58,690 --> 00:14:00,190
Fed up, huh?

210
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:01,820
Girl, you're my kind of flashy!

211
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:04,820
I like you! Welcome aboard!

212
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:10,620
Infiltration successful!

213
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:13,170
Pirates are all such suckers!

214
00:14:16,130 --> 00:14:17,960
Why am I in a cage?

215
00:14:20,590 --> 00:14:22,550
I feel great today!

216
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,930
Girl, what's your name?

217
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:25,930
Nami!

218
00:14:25,930 --> 00:14:27,300
Fantastic!

219
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:30,060
Let's hold a welcome
party for Nami here!

220
00:14:30,060 --> 00:14:31,180
And make it flashy!

221
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:52,040
What's wrong?! This
celebration's in your honor!

222
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,540
Eat up!

223
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:56,040
Yes! Thank you!

224
00:14:57,040 --> 00:15:01,050
Just gotta find the right moment
to take back the map.

225
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:04,720
While I'm at it, maybe I'll swipe
the rest of Buggy's treasure too!

226
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:08,640
Dammit!

227
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:20,070
Now this is flashy!

228
00:15:20,070 --> 00:15:21,150
Men!

229
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:25,240
Prepare a Special Buggy Ball!

230
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:44,730
All set, sir!

231
00:15:45,470 --> 00:15:47,970
Wh-What's about to happen?

232
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:51,100
Observe the might of the Buggy Ball!

233
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:51,720
Light it.

234
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:15,290
What was that explosion?

235
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:18,790
It's one of our captain's
beloved Buggy Balls!

236
00:16:19,420 --> 00:16:21,290
Buggy Balls?!

237
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,220
Truly flashy!

238
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:36,850
With Buggy Balls and my devil fruit,

239
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:39,850
the Grand Line will be
mine for the taking!

240
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:41,060
Right, Nami?!

241
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:42,940
Y-Yes! Of course!

242
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:44,530
Say what?!

243
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:45,280
Huh?!

244
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:48,240
But I'm the one who's gonna
take over the Grand Line!

245
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:50,160
What?

246
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,570
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

247
00:16:52,990 --> 00:16:54,540
You idiot!

248
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:00,000
I see why you're sick of him, Nami!

249
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,670
You got that right!

250
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:04,920
He's super naive
and dumb as a rock, too!

251
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:07,510
I couldn't put up with it anymore.

252
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:08,590
Naturally!

253
00:17:08,590 --> 00:17:13,300
Well then, take a Buggy Ball
and blow your old boss to smithereens!

254
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:14,300
Huh?

255
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:19,770
It'll also prove your loyalty to me.

256
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:20,440
Do it!

257
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:30,070
N-No, that's okay!

258
00:17:30,070 --> 00:17:34,280
C'mon, this is a welcoming party!
Let's get back to the fun!

259
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:36,540
Do it.

260
00:17:36,540 --> 00:17:38,700
This is my kind of welcoming party.

261
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,840
– Fire! Fire! Fire!
– Fire! Fire! Fire!

262
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:49,590
If I don't shoot, I'll be killed!

263
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:54,970
But if I do shoot,
I'm no better than a pirate.

264
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,970
Now light it with some flashy style!

265
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:11,070
– Fire! Fire! Fire!
– Fire! Fire! Fire!

266
00:18:11,070 --> 00:18:13,950
Nami! Don't wimp out on me now!

267
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:17,780
You okay?

268
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,580
Your hands are shaking!

269
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:25,540
This is what happens when you don't
have the guts to take on pirates.

270
00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:27,790
The guts to do what?

271
00:18:27,790 --> 00:18:30,010
To murder in cold blood?!

272
00:18:30,010 --> 00:18:31,840
Is that what it means to be a pirate?!

273
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:32,720
No!

274
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,510
The guts to put your life on the line!

275
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:42,680
– Fire! Fire! Fire!
– Fire! Fire! Fire!

276
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,860
Hey, new chick! Quit being a tease!

277
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:48,690
This is how you light it!

278
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:01,370
Crap! I didn't mean to...

279
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:05,670
Nami! What's the meaning of this?!

280
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,130
I'm sorry!

281
00:19:07,130 --> 00:19:09,880
What?! Apologizing won't fix things!

282
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,420
What's with you?

283
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:13,510
Now you're saving me?

284
00:19:13,510 --> 00:19:14,880
Don't be dense!

285
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,510
The situation called for this!

286
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:21,010
I just didn't want to wind up
like these low-life pirates!

287
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:22,850
Oh, the situation!

288
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:25,440
Pirates took the life
of someone dear to me!

289
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:27,310
As if I'd ever become one!

290
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,440
Oh, so that's why...

291
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,190
Huh?

292
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,190
It's lit!

293
00:19:34,150 --> 00:19:37,610
Keep your ridicule to a minimum, girl!

294
00:19:37,610 --> 00:19:38,950
Give her a flashy death!

295
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:41,450
– Yahoo!
– Yahoo!

296
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:47,170
– A flashy death!
– A flashy death!

297
00:19:47,170 --> 00:19:48,330
– C'mon!
– Get her!

298
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:51,380
W-Water! Water! Water! Water!

299
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,720
Not good!

300
00:20:04,930 --> 00:20:05,980
You're...

301
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:12,230
Behind you!

302
00:20:12,230 --> 00:20:14,320
– Flashy death!
– Flashy death!

303
00:20:20,620 --> 00:20:22,080
Hey, now...

304
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:26,580
How many goons does it take
to bring down one girl?

305
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:28,790
Zoro!

306
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:35,880
You hurt?

307
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:37,420
Huh...?

308
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:39,590
Are you hurt?

309
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:42,220
N-No, I'm fine.

310
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:44,390
Whew, what a relief!

311
00:20:44,390 --> 00:20:46,180
How'd you find us?

312
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:47,770
Hurry and get me outta here!

313
00:20:47,770 --> 00:20:50,770
Why are you always
just messing around?

314
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:53,860
First some bird flies off with you,
and now you're in a cage?

315
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:55,400
It was pretty cool, actually.

316
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:57,900
– Zoro?
– Zo...

317
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:00,570
Th-That's what he
just called him, right?

318
00:21:00,990 --> 00:21:05,490
The crew member he mentioned...
was Pirate Hunter Zoro?

319
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,750
What's going on?!

320
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:10,830
So you're Zoro?

321
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:15,210
What do you want? Are you
after my head or something?

322
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:17,840
Nope. Not interested.

323
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,930
I gave up pirate-hunting.

324
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:25,310
I'm interested, though!
Killing you should boost my rep!

325
00:21:26,810 --> 00:21:29,020
I wouldn't try it. You'll die.

326
00:21:29,020 --> 00:21:31,730
Oh? That so?

327
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:36,230
Guess words aren't enough for you...

328
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,110
Whoo! Get him, Captain!

329
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:41,740
Captain Buggy!

330
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:55,670
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!

331
00:21:56,170 --> 00:21:59,340
A flashy death for you!

332
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:15,860
I cut him almost too easily...

333
00:22:15,860 --> 00:22:17,480
Whoa!

334
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,280
He was no match...!

335
00:22:19,780 --> 00:22:20,860
No way...

336
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,540
What's with them?

337
00:22:32,540 --> 00:22:34,170
Wh-Why are they...?

338
00:22:34,170 --> 00:22:37,290
Their captain's been killed,
but they're laughing!

339
00:22:37,290 --> 00:22:38,630
Hey!

340
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:40,880
What's so damn funny?!

341
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:50,520
Zoro!

342
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:53,060
Is that an arm?!

343
00:22:53,060 --> 00:22:55,850
What the hell?!

344
00:22:59,110 --> 00:23:01,030
The Chop-Chop Fruit.

345
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:05,360
That's the name of the devil fruit I ate!

346
00:23:06,870 --> 00:23:10,870
I'm a splitting man! I can't be cut!

347
00:23:13,710 --> 00:23:16,250
His body parts reassembled!

348
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:19,710
I thought devil fruits
were only a myth!

349
00:23:19,710 --> 00:23:21,300
A splitting man?!

350
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,960
You mean he's a freak?!

351
00:23:25,930 --> 00:23:29,600
I didn't hit anything vital,
but that's a pretty serious wound!

352
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,640
I win!

353
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:36,600
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!

354
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,020
You're too much, Captain!

355
00:23:33,890 --> 00:23:36,600
Buggy! Buggy!

356
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:41,070
Crap! The tables have turned!

357
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:44,950
If we don't do something
quick, we're all dead!

358
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:49,160
That one actually hurt a bit...

359
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:58,080
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!
– Buggy! Buggy! Buggy!

360
00:23:58,080 --> 00:24:00,420
Stabbing him from behind isn't fair,

361
00:24:00,420 --> 00:24:02,050
Big Nose!

362
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,340
Y-You idiot!

363
00:24:07,340 --> 00:24:09,340
Don't call him that!

364
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:17,810
Who's... got a big nose?!

365
00:24:19,190 --> 00:24:19,850
Luffy!

366
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:22,820
Buggy!

367
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:27,280
I'm so gonna kick your ass!

368
00:24:31,530 --> 00:24:33,120
Kick my ass?

369
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,790
You're a real riot!

370
00:24:34,790 --> 00:24:37,910
All three of you are gonna
die here, you know!

371
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:40,750
And just how will my ass
get kicked, pray tell?!

372
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:43,040
Well?! Well?! Well?!

373
00:24:47,630 --> 00:24:50,590
It's no use... It's all over...

374
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:55,220
I refuse to die!

375
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,310
Run, Zoro!

376
00:24:57,310 --> 00:24:58,310
What?!

377
00:24:58,310 --> 00:25:01,560
Wait! He came here to save you!

378
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,060
What are you gonna do?!

379
00:25:08,990 --> 00:25:09,990
Understood.

380
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:12,370
Nothing makes sense anymore!

381
00:25:12,370 --> 00:25:14,740
This is why I hate pirates!

382
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,950
Don't even think about it, dumbasses!

383
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:18,870
You're not going anywhere!

384
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:26,880
How foolish!

385
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:30,220
Your three-sword style
has no effect on...

386
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:33,390
Hey! Listen when someone's talking!

387
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:53,410
Oh, crap! The cannon's
pointed this way!

388
00:25:53,870 --> 00:25:55,160
Hey! Light it!

389
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:55,830
What?!

390
00:25:55,830 --> 00:25:56,790
Hurry!

391
00:25:56,790 --> 00:25:57,450
O-Okay!

392
00:25:58,370 --> 00:25:59,830
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

393
00:25:59,830 --> 00:26:04,040
There's still a Special Buggy Ball in there!

394
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,340
You lit it!

395
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:12,010
Ahh! Wait! No! Stop!

396
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:13,680
Stop!

397
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:32,570
Hey, Zoro. You're hurt, you know...

398
00:26:32,820 --> 00:26:35,200
Just shut up and sit tight!

399
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,490
I'm gonna do things my way!

400
00:26:43,210 --> 00:26:45,670
Who is this guy?!

401
00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:50,670
Luffy... who is she?

402
00:26:51,010 --> 00:26:53,220
Oh, she's our navigator!

403
00:26:54,340 --> 00:26:56,300
Stop joking around!

404
00:26:56,300 --> 00:26:58,470
Who are you guys?!

405
00:26:58,470 --> 00:27:00,180
Move...

406
00:27:01,270 --> 00:27:02,600
You're in the way!

407
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:17,320
Why would you go that far?

408
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:18,830
You're a pirate!

409
00:08:56,310 --> 00:09:00,480
Nami, a Pirate Thief

410
00:08:56,310 --> 00:09:00,480
Nami, a Pirate Thief

